North Korea’s foreign minister told the United Nations on Saturday that maintaining sanctions has only increased mistrust of the United States and that there is no way the country would unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons in such circumstances.
Ri Jongho told the UN General Assembly last year that North Korea had taken “significant and generous steps,” including halting nuclear and missile testing, closing nuclear testing sites, and promising not to expand its nuclear arsenal and scope of nuclear technology.
