“America insists that we start with nuclear disarmament, increases the pressure with sanctions to impose its will on us, and also protests against the declaration of an end to the war,” he said.
“The idea that sanctions can bring us to our knees is a pipe dream of people who don’t know us.
“The problem is that non-relieving sanctions only increase our suspicions.”
Ri did not mention plans for a second summit between Kim and Trump, which the US president specifically mentioned at the UN earlier this week.
